      "settings": {
        "checksum": "fc5ca4caaff71139648c5c11284172a0ac2af87a3f235d6da3b7a8bd13ff42b1_1_1_0_0__1",
        "gg0045cZav__text": "<p>Until you decompress those vertebrae and rehydrate those discs, the pain always returns.</p>",
        "gg4YoJ0BCta_text": "<p>Your cervical discs are like jelly donuts between your vertebrae. When they’re hydrated, you move without pain.</p>",
        "ggA8gdNg1BQ_text": "<p><strong>Burning sensations down your arms</strong></p>",
        "ggGkzemG1js_text": "<span style=\"color:#055BDC;\"><strong>Your Spine Is LITERALLY Suffocating</strong></span>",
        "ggGxVIgVHqv_text": "<p>Stretches don’t rehydrate discs. Pills just mask pain. Even surgery can’t restore disc hydration.</p>",
